---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="How Econified Tools Work | Methodology & Transparency" description="Understand the logic behind Econified calculators, from local processing to adjustable assumptions.">
  <main class="container">
    <div class="glass-panel content-section">
      <h1>How Econified Tools Work</h1>
      
      <p>
        Econified tools are designed to provide transparent calculations based on user inputs.
      </p>

      <h2>Local Processing</h2>
      <p>
        All calculations run directly in your browser. No financial inputs are sent to a server or stored by Econified.
      </p>

      <h2>Adjustable Assumptions</h2>
      <p>
        Many real-world decisions depend on assumptions such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Working hours</li>
        <li>Weeks worked per year</li>
        <li>Billable time</li>
        <li>Compensation structure</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Econified allows these values to be adjusted so users can explore different scenarios.
      </p>

      <h2>Calculation Transparency</h2>
      <p>
        Each tool includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The formula used</li>
        <li>Assumptions behind the calculation</li>
        <li>Explanatory insights</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This allows users to understand how results are generated.
      </p>

      <h2>Intended Use</h2>
      <p>
        The tools are intended for educational and informational exploration only and should not be considered professional advice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .content-section ul {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .content-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
